<subSubSection id="C348A2CCD649DC0222CEFFA4B3E26690" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEDF147D649DC0222CEFFA4B3E26690" blockId="14.[151,1436,751,1018]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC0222CEFFA4B33B66C3" bold="true" box="[198,319,911,937]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC0223DAFFBBB10266C0" authority="Marseul, 1870" authorityName="Marseul" authorityYear="1870" box="[466,774,912,938]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Lydoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC0223DAFFBBB04F66C3" box="[466,587,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lydoceras</emphasis>
Marseul, 1870
</taxonomicName>
, which is under revision (Bologna unpublished), is an Afrotropical element strictly related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC022056FF93B0B866BB" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[606,700,952,977]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC022056FF93B0B866BB" box="[606,700,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is clearly distinct by the shape of antennae, which are progressively narrowed at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
